postcontent:
JAN 29 UPDATE:  this pistol is also for sale on Gunbroker, and it has at least one bid so far, so it WILL sell thru GB in 2 days, and is thus no longer for sale locally via this channel.   If you want it, bid on it at GB:
http://www.gunbroker.com/Auction/ViewItem.aspx?Item=388524410


Step up to one of the world's most powerful handguns: the .50 Action Express, considerably larger than .44 Magnum. 

I got this pistol last year.  After shooting it some, I decided it needs a younger, stronger owner.  It's got the ported barrel, and the recoil isn't ridiculously bad, but firing it hurts my wrist after a few  rounds, so I think I will pass it on and get something else.

Very good condition, with some minor handling marks and marks along the frame from slide travel.

Weight: 46.2 oz
Length: 10.75 in
Barrel Length: 6.5 in
Width: 1.375 in

Includes one new box of Hornady Custom ammo - 300 gr XTP/HP with 17 live rounds and 3 empty cases.  Includes 2 magazines (1 shown in pic)

FTF only, cash only

It's a quite rare handgun - no others listed on Armslist in entire USA,  There's only 1 of these listed on GB and it's $2000 BIN, so this is quite a bargain, plus no shipping, no delay, no 4473.

Here's some info about the gun, if you're not familiar with it:
The AMT Automag V is a large single action semi-automatic pistol made by Arcadia Machine and Tool (AMT) in Irwindale, CA.  The weapon was created by Harry Sanford, who also invented the original .44 AutoMag pistol. One of the extremely small number of handguns that fire a .50 caliber cartridge, it is also one of the few semi automatic guns that fires the .50 Action Express cartridge, it is said to be "the most ergonomic and lightweight of all of those autoloaders".   Its built-in compensator ports in the barrel assist in keeping muzzle rise to tolerable levels. The recoil, however, is still surprisingly brisk even for the most experienced shooter. The Automag V has a 5 shot magazine capacity (5+1 total) and is, like all of the AMT pistols, made primarily of cast stainless steel.

postcontent:
Just received from the distributor, a brand new Walther PPK/S. It is under warranty, and you will be the first owner.

I am letting go of it at the wholesale price because of the tool marks in the barrel near the throat. These appear to be standard in PPKs and PPK/S pistols - I have returned the first two (PPKs) to the distributors after discovering them, got these two (PPK/S) from a different distributor, and it is the same.

So, if you are planning to by a new PPK/S, you can at least save some money, as it appears that all currently produced guns are the same.

This describes the problem: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/BadWalthers.aspx

My price (wholesale) was $543 + $7 shipping. You will also pay the tax, obviously, as this is a new gun in my FFL inventory.

FAQ

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to
www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the
appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?
A. If you see this ad, most likely. The firearms are reserved for pickup on my web site,
by making an appointment to buy. Someone could be doing it right now, and first person
to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy,
read the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just
before you, I will notify you within a short time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you
shortly.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK WHETHER THE GUN IS STILL AVAILABLE! I WILL NOT RESPOND.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy,
read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only
times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other
time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to
offer them to me at well below wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military
as well as highly accurate, competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see
here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Q. Is the price firm? Will you take XXX (70% of the asking price)?
A. The price is firm.

A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area.

title: For Sale:  Yugo SKS w/ some great upgrades
postcontent: This is a Yugoslavian SKS. All matching numbers gun. I removed the stock and meticulously hand sanded every blemish out of the beautiful Baltic Birch. Then I applied 15 coats of Tung Oil Gloss Finish. (one coat per day for 15 days) Between each coat, I buffed the entire stock with 0000 steel wool to get a beautiful resulting high gloss and durable finish. This is the kind of Finish put on very high dollar rifles. You will not find a more beautiful SKS, anywhere. The firing pin was replaced with a Murray's stainless steel firing pin and spring set. The gas valve was replaced with a Murray's stainless steel gas valve. The original parts that were replaced come with the rifle upon sale. I sent the trigger assembly to Bill Springfield , (http://www.triggerwork.net/sksrifles.html) and he did a great trigger job, reducing the length of pull and removing all grittiness in the trigger. Also he reduced the trigger pull from over 8lbs. to just a hair over 4lbs. Needless to say, this SKS shoots like a dream. By far the smoothest, most accurate SKS I have shot in 40 years of shooting. Included are : a Tapco 20 rd. magazine, one dust cover scope mount with a no-name 4x scope, and another dust cover scope mount with a BSA Red Dot scope. Personally, I prefer the stock sights, but to each their own. You wont find a prettier, smoother shooting , or more accurate SKS. The bore shows very little wear and the accuracy proves it. Comes with original web sling and original magazine. This is the model with grenade launcher , grenade sights and phosphorescent night sights, original blade bayonet, and correct cleaning kit (in the buttstock) and cleaning rod. I know I am asking a premium price, but when you see this rifle in person, it is a gem.

Adjustable back-up sights are integrated and can be folded down in to the Picatinny rail, and the front post is Tritium for improved visibility. All metal parts are treated for corrosion resistance.
